        // ── Advanced Reference (Reference) ───────────────────────────────
        await GetOrCreateModule(new TrainingModule
        {
            Title = "Getting Around Faster — Advanced Reference",
            Slug = "navigation-reference",
            Summary = "A deeper reference for power users: searching well, working the side menu, keyboard shortcuts, breadcrumbs, sharing views, and the theme.",
            ContentType = TrainingContentType.Reference,
            EstimatedMinutes = 4,
            IsPublished = true,
            SortOrder = 90,
            AppRoutes = """["/dashboard"]""",
            Tags = """["navigation","reference","advanced"]""",
            ContentJson = """{"body":"## Searching Like a Pro\n\nSearch is the fastest way to reach anything you can name. Press Ctrl+K from any page to open it, type, and go. A few habits pay off:\n\n- **Search across everything at once.** One search covers jobs, parts, customers, vendors, and purchase orders. You don't have to be on the right page first — results come back grouped by type, so a part and a customer with the same name stay easy to tell apart.\n- **Use the number, not the name.** A job or PO number is unique, so it jumps straight to one result. Names can match several records.\n- **Keep typing to narrow.** The list shrinks as you add characters. Add a second word (a customer plus a part) to zero in when a single term is too broad.\n- **Move without the mouse.** Arrow keys walk the results; Enter opens the highlighted one; Escape closes search and leaves you where you were.\n\n## Working the Side Menu\n\nThe side menu rewards a little setup. Widen it when you're learning where things live, then narrow it back to icons once the icons are familiar — you get more room for your work and still see the current page highlighted. Forge remembers the width per browser, so a shared kiosk and your own laptop can each keep their own setting.\n\nGroups only open one at a time as you click into them, which keeps a long menu short. The group for the page you're on opens on its own, so you always see your neighbors — the other pages in the same area. If a group or item you expect is missing, it's because that feature isn't turned on for your company or isn't part of your role; it's not hidden by accident.\n\n## Breadcrumbs — Stepping Back Up\n\nMany pages show a trail near the top: the path from a broad list down to the one record you opened. Click any earlier step in the trail to jump back up a level without hunting through the menu — handy when you drilled from a customer into one of their orders and want to get back to the customer. The trail always reflects where you actually are, so it's a reliable \"where am I\" cue on deep pages.\n\n## Keyboard Shortcuts Worth Learning\n\nPress / (forward slash) anywhere to see the full list. The ones that save the most time day to day:\n\n- **Ctrl+K** — jump to search from anywhere.\n- **/** — open the shortcuts list itself, when you forget one.\n- **Escape** — back out of the open panel, dialog, or search without changing anything.\n- **Q then a letter** — quick jumps to the pages you hit most: Q then D for Dashboard, K for the Board, B for Backlog, P for Parts, I for Inventory, R for Reports, T for Time. Tap Q, then the letter — you don't hold them together.\n\n## Sharing and Bookmarking a View\n\nYour exact view lives in the web address — the tab you're on, the record you opened, the filters and sort you set, and the page you're reading. That has real, practical payoff:\n\n- **Send a teammate the same view.** Copy the address and paste it into chat or email. They land on your filtered, sorted list — no \"scroll down to the third one\" instructions needed.\n- **Bookmark the views you live in.** Save a bookmark to your filtered Backlog or a specific job, and it reopens exactly there next time.\n- **Refresh safely.** Reloading keeps your place — filters and the open record survive, so a stray refresh never sends you back to square one.\n- **Back and forward just work.** The browser's back button steps you through where you've been, the same as any website.\n\n## The Theme, and Why It's Yours Alone\n\nThe sun/moon switch in the header flips between light and dark. Dark is the default and reads well on a dim floor or a bright shop; light suits a sunlit office. Your choice is saved to you and follows you across your open tabs and your next sign-in — it doesn't change what anyone else sees. If your device is set to reduce motion, animations turn themselves off, so the app stays comfortable without any setting to find.","sections":[]}"""
        });

